MC3T3-E1 cells were maintained in α- MEM containing 10% FBS and 1% PS (growth medium), in a constant humidity atmosphere of 5% CO 2 at 37 C. Cells were seeded in 12-well culture plates at a density of 1 × 105 cells/well for 24 h. When cells reached 100% confluence, the growth medium was replaced with osteogenic differentiation medium (growth medium with 10 mM β- glycerol phosphate, 50 μg/ml ascorbic acid and 100 nM dexamethasone) for 7 or 16 days (
;
). The osteogenic differentiation medium was refreshed every two days.
